goals.question: What is the correlation between net generation and year?

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data, palette='bright')
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.legend(title='Source', loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['source']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="source", y="net_generation", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Source', ylabel='Average Net Generation')
    plt.title('What is the average net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    for i in ax.containers:
        ax.bar_label(i, label_type='edge', fontsize=10, padding=2)
    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    chart = sns.catplot(x="year", y="net_generation", hue="source", data=data, kind="bar", height=6, aspect=1.5)
    chart.set(title='What is the distribution of net generation for each year by source?')
    chart.set_axis_labels("Year", "Net Generation")
    chart._legend.set_title('Source')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.
